ndependence Party\".\n\n==References==\n{{No footnotes|date=April 2008}}\n*''Times Guide to the House of Commons 1979''\n*{{Rayment-hc|date=March 2012}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{hansard-contribs | mr-michael-brotherton | Michael Brotherton }}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-par|uk}}\n{{s-bef | before = [[Jeffrey Archer]] }}\n{{s-ttl\n  | title  = [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Louth, Lincolnshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Louth]]\n  | years  = [[October 1974 United Kingdom general election|Oct 1974]]\u2013[[1983 United Kingdom general election|1983]]\n}}\n{{s-non | reason = Constituency abolished }}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brotherton, Michael}}\n[[Category:1931 births]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Royal Navy officers]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1974\u20131979]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1979\u20131983]]\n[[Category:UK Independence Party people]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEarly political activity:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1967-1968 \u2192 1967\u20131968", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Brotherton"}
