ne Mad\n| note13 = alternative version\n| length13 = 4:39\n| title14 = Instrumental outtake\n| writer14 = Scanlon, Hanley\n| length14 = 3:46\n| title15 = Service\n| note15 = instrumental demo\n| length15 = 4:40\n| title16 = Glam-Racket\n| note16 = instrumental demo\n| length16 = 3:21\n| title17 = Lost in Music\n| note17 = mix 3\n| length17 = 4:40\n| title18 = Lost in Music\n| note18 = mix 7\n| length18 = 4:39\n| title19 = Lost in Music\n| note19 = mix 14\n| length19 = 4:28\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n;The Fall\n* [[Mark E. Smith]] \u2013 vocals, tapes, production <small>(2, 10)</small>\n* [[Craig Scanlon]] \u2013 guitar\n* [[Steve Hanley]] \u2013 bass guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Simon Wolstencroft]] \u2013 drums, programming\n* Dave Bush \u2013 keyboards, programming, backing vocals\n;Additional personnel\n* Rex Sargeant \u2013 production <small>(1, 4\u20139, 11)</small>\n* [[Simon Rogers]] \u2013 production <small>(3, 12)</small>\n* [[:fr:Pascal Le Gras|Pascal Le Gras]] \u2013 cover art\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{The Fall}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Infotainment Scan}}\n[[Category:1993 albums]]\n[[Category:The Fall (band) albums]]\n[[Category:Matador Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "Cnwilliams", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:Steve Hanley\u2192Steve Hanley (musician)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Infotainment_Scan"}
